State updates asynchronous hote hain:- State updates asynchronous hote hain” ka matlab React state ko turant update nahi karta. Pehle current function complete hota hai, fir React state update karta hai aur component re-render karta hai.

State React component ki internal changing value hoti hai. Iska use tab karte hain jab UI me koi value time ke saath change hoti ho, jaise counter, input, login status.

const [count, setCount] = useState(0);

Yahan count state hai aur setCount usko update karta hai.

State direct change nahi karte, setCount use karte hain. Jab state update hoti hai, component dobara render hota hai aur UI me new value dikhne lagti hai.

Flow:

Pehle component render hota hai with count = 0
setCount(count + 1) call hota hai
React update request store karta hai
Function complete hota hai
Fir component second time render hota hai with updated value

Isliye total 2 render hote hain:

Initial render
State change ke baad render







