useEffect :-
useEffect is a hook that lets us perform side effects in function components. It takes a function and a dependency array. The effect runs after render. If the dependency array is empty, it runs only once on mount. If dependencies are provided, it runs again when those values change. We can return a cleanup function to cancel timers, remove event listeners, or avoid memory leaks. Common uses: data fetching, subscriptions, manually changing the DOM.

useEffect(() => {
  const timer = setInterval(() => console.log('tick'), 1000);
  return () => clearInterval(timer);
}, []);


useEffect एक React Hook है जो functional components में side effects perform करने देता है – जैसे API calls, timers, event listeners, या DOM updates।

Syntax बताइए:-


useEffect(() => {
  // side effect logic
  return () => {
    // cleanup logic (optional)
  };
}, [dependencies]);

