3. Suspense

---

Jab lazy component load hota hai tab thoda time lag sakta hai.

Us time tak user ko blank screen na dikhe,
isliye Suspense use karte hain.

Suspense ek temporary loading UI dikhata hai.

Syntax:

```jsx

<Suspense fallback={<h1>Loading...</h1>}>

\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\&#x20; <About />

</Suspense>

```

Yahan:

* About component load ho raha hai
* Tab tak "Loading..." show hoga
* Jab About load ho jayega
* Tab About component show ho jayega

Flow:

About load ho raha hai
→ Loading... show

About load ho gaya
→ Actual component show

---

4. Teeno ka Relation

---

Code Splitting
→ Code ko alag-alag parts me todta hai

Lazy Loading
→ Un parts ko zarurat par load karta hai

Suspense
→ Load hone tak loading dikhata hai

Short Form:

* Code Splitting = Divide code
* Lazy Loading = Load only when needed
* Suspense = Show loading until loaded

---

